},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet suffers from hunger all day","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 5, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar reported: I saw the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, spend the entire day suffering from hunger. The Prophet could not find even the worst dates with which to fill his stomach. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2978 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0642\u064e\u062f\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":784,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/15\/ahl-al-bayt-eat-fill\/","url_meta":{"origin":34995,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet\u2019s family rarely ate to their fill","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 15, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The family of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him,\u00a0never ate to their fill of wheat bread for three consecutive nights, ever since they had come to Medina, until he passed away. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6089, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2970 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25997,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/02\/prophet-many-nights-hungry\/","url_meta":{"origin":34995,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet spent many nights hungry","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 2, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would spend several nights in a row with an empty stomach, and his family would not find anything for dinner. Most of their bread was made from barley. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2360 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34527,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/28\/prophet-suffers-with-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":34995,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet suffers in poverty with his companions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 28, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Talhah reported: We complained about hunger to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and we lifted our garments to reveal stones tied to our stomachs, so the Messenger of Allah lifted his garment to reveal two stones. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2371 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2935,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/18\/death-only-his-deeds-remain\/","url_meta":{"origin":34995,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Death: After death, only his deeds remain","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThree things follow a deceased person. Two of them return and one remains. His family, his wealth, and his deeds follow him. His family and wealth return, but his deeds remain.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6149,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":281,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/12\/22\/world-prison-believer\/","url_meta":{"origin":34995,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Hereafter: Worldly life is a prison for the believer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 22, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cThe world is a prison for the believer and a paradise for the unbeliever.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2956 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e\u00a0\u0627\u0644\u062f\u064f\u0651\u0646\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0633\u0650\u062c\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0624\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\